claim: Flublok ensures identical antigenic match with WHO- and FDA-selected flu strains.
explanation: A table comparing vaccine effectiveness (VE) percentages and 95% confidence intervals of recombinant quadrivalent influenza vaccine (RIV4), standard-dose quadrivalent influenza vaccine (SD-IIV4), and combinations with high-dose and adjuvanted vaccines, stratified by age group (18–64 years and ≥65 years) and demographics. The table presents clinical effectiveness data and does not provide any information on antigenic match to WHO- or FDA-selected strains, so it does not support the claim. Note: Limited to VE outcomes; no strain matching or regulatory selection details are shown.
